# Never ship host build artifacts or local deps into the Docker context.
# The deps stage runs `pnpm install` inside the image; if host node_modules
# leak in via COPY they clash with the already-materialised directories
# (e.g. `cannot replace to directory .../node_modules/socket.io with file`).

**/node_modules
**/.next
**/dist
**/build
**/.turbo
**/.cache
**/.pnpm-store
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Python
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/.venv
**/venv

# Git / editor / OS
.git
.gitignore
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Logs & env (env is injected at runtime via docker-compose)
**/*.log
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Docs / tests don't belong in runtime images, but we keep them for build
# context simplicity. Only hard-exclude the heavy stuff above.
